    "methodology": "Productivity index measures total NHS output (weighted activity across elective, emergency, outpatient, mental health, community) per unit of input (staff, intermediate consumption, capital). Indexed to 2014 = 100. Staff figures are full-time equivalent per 1,000 population. Output per worker adjusts total output index by FTE headcount.",
